    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Actions or processes resulting in the change of form in an animal or its parts, during post-embryonic development. The term is used for the process of transformation from an immature form to a different adult form that many insects and other invertebrates, and some vertebrates (e.g., frogs), undergo in the course of maturing. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
